The paper deals with the performance analysis of multi-hop relay communication channels, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of multiple antennas at each terminal also suggests the possibility of exploring signal processing (cs.SI) and communication theory (cs.COMM). Finally, the large-system analysis method used in the paper is a technique commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.MA).
